-- Bucher Industries, Georg Fischer, Novartis: Swiss Equity Market Preview
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2010-12-21T07:35:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/bucher-industries-georg-fischer-novartis-swiss-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share prices are
from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies fell 0.3 percent to 6,521.25 yesterday. The
broader  Swiss Performance Index  lost 0.1 percent to 5,852.96.  Bucher Industries AG  (BUCN SW): The world’s biggest maker
of feed-mixing equipment won a 40 million Swiss-franc ($42
million) order in India. The shares advanced 0.3 percent to
171.4 francs.  Georg Fischer AG  (FI/N SW): Europe’s largest maker of iron
castings for cars named Jean-Pierre Wilmes to the board. The
shares declined 0.7 percent to 545.5 francs.  Novartis AG  (NOVN VX): The Swiss drugmaker’s Tasigna
medicine has been approved in Japan for use in a form of newly
diagnosed chronic myeloid leukemia, the company said. The shares
lost 0.5 percent to 56.45 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Zurich at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 